                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clip that secures the freon hose to the radiator and discard. (See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9116021">Figure 1</hotlnk>.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the freon hose from the compressor and condenser and discard.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the threads on the fittings of the new freon hose and connect the hose to the
                    compressor and condenser. Tighten the fittings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the new clip secure the hose to the radiator in the same location as the hose
                    removed. The new clip will secure the rubber portion of the hose instead of the metal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9116021" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9116021.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Freon Hose Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CONDENSER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. METAL PORTION OF FREON HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. RUBBER PORTION OF FREON HOSE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
